cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new optimizer that combines the idea of "learning to optimize" and traditional Adam optimizer, which falls under the category of neural networks and optimization algorithms. Hence, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the application of the proposed optimizer in various network training, such as multilayer perceptron, CNN, and LSTM, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely categories.
